1.Install relevant dependency packages, JDK, and configure the Java environment

Description: The JDK is a software development kit for the Java language, which contains the Java Virtual Machine (JVM). 
The compiled Java source program can form Java bytecode, and as long as the JDK is installed, these bytecode files can be interpreted by JVM, 
thus realizing the cross-platform nature of Java

tar xzf jdk-7u65-linux-x64.gz -C /usr/src
cd /usr/src
mv jdk1.7.0_65/ /usr/local/java

vim /etc/profile.d/fava.sh
export JAVA_HOME=/usr/local/java      //设置Java根目录
export PATH=$PATH:$JAVA_HOME/bin      //在PATH环境变量中添加JAVA根目录下的bin/子目录
source /etc/profile.d/java.sh

2.Install and configure Tomcat

tar xzf apache-tomcat-*.tar.gz -C /usr/src
mv /usr/src/apache-tomcat-* /usr/local/tomcat7
/usr/local/tomcat7/bin/startup.sh             //启动Tomcat

3.Tomcat configuration related instructions

| - bin / : store Windows or Linux platform startup and shutdown Tomcat script file
| - conf / : Tomcat server various global configuration file
| - lib / : deposit Tomcat run need libraries (JARS)
| - logs: deposit Tomcat implementation of the LOG file
| - webapps: Tomcat's main Web publishing directory
| - work: deposit JSP compiled class files

4.Conf/the contents of the file

Catalina. policy: Permission control configuration file
Catalina.properties: Tomcat properties profile
XML: Context configuration file
Logging.properties: Log related configuration files
Server.xml: The master configuration file
Tomcat -Users.xml: Manager-GUI to manage user profiles (Tomcat provides a Manager-GUI interface after installation, which can be accessed via this file configuration)
Web.xml: Tomcat's Servlet, Servlet-Mapping, Filter, MIME and other related configuration.

Note: When deploying other Tomcat, versions must be consistent.
